A 43-year-old Lake Wales man riding a motorized scooter died Wednesday when troopers say he collided with a pickup truck at a Land O’Lakes intersection. The man was riding the scooter south on Livingston Road about 9:30 p.m. when he failed to stop for a red light and crashed into a pickup truck headed east on State Road 54. according to the Florida Highway Patrol. The scooter rider died from his injuries. The 62-year-old Brandon man driving the pickup was not injured. The Florida Highway Patrol typically does not release the names of people involved in crashes due to Marsy’s Law.